subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Test oval or round (TL = 
6.6 to 9.8 mm
; TH = 
2.6 to 8 mm
), usually low and flat, oral region slightly concave (
Fig. 11
A–D). Test covered by short, slender, hyaline spines (
Fig. 11A
). Petals small and open distally (
Fig. 11C, E
). Madreporite slightly prominent. Genital and ocular pores of same size (
Fig. 11C, E
). Four genital and five ocular pores form a conspicuous circle or pentagon around the madreporite (
Fig. 11C, E
). Primary spines elongate and lanceolate. Miliary spines shorter than primary spines, with terminal crown. Peristome central, circular, three times size of periproct (
Fig. 11B, D
). Periproct small, circular, inframarginal, and usually covered by 5 to 6 regular plates that never bear spines. Phyllodes lacking.

